    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Re-engage open deals with Google Sheets and Telegram\n\n**Pattern:** Reminders & Follow-ups · **Level:** Core · **Trigger:** Scheduled\n\n## What it does\nRe-engage open deals with Google Sheets and Telegram. It runs automatically on a schedule.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual auto-responders is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nDaily Schedule → Normalize Email Payload → Slot Free? → Record Booking → Send Confirmation (Telegram) → Hold Until Reminder Time → Send Reminder (Telegram) → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to reminders & follow-ups without manual effort\n- Anyone automating auto-responders in marketing\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Runs 24/7 in the background\n- Standardizes the process every time\n- Responds in seconds\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: Google OAuth2 / service account; Slack OAuth2; Telegram bot token.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.",
        "width": 480,
        "height": 900
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -830,
        80
      ],
      "id": "1ea1d4b9-3769-f8ab-4eab-3b3f9d936a1c",
      "name": "📘 Workflow Overview"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 3
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -230,
        -260
      ],
      "id": "eeb56ed0-6fff-ba33-bae6-b074058f223e",
      "name": "🛟 Error handling & retries"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## ⏱ Rate limiting\n\nWork is batched and spaced with Wait so provider quotas aren't tripped. If you hit 429s, lower the batch size or raise the wait — throughput drops, reliability rises.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 1
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        190,
